Communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Data by country, area, or territory for 31 Mar 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20Mar31_1617298717.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 29.2% of daily case numbers and 35.8% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 55.73 million cases. The USA reported over 61 000 cases over the last 24 hours followed by Brazil with 38 927 cases. 11 additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours (Colombia, Argentina, Mexico, Peru, Chile, Paraguay, Uruguay, Ecuador, Cuba, Venezuela, and Canada), and an additional 2 countries (Bolivia, and Honduras) reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 45.2% of daily case numbers and 48.4% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 44.80 million. Many countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Belgium (4 cases), Israel, Switzerland (3 cases), and Kazakhstan, among others. Turkey reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Poland, France, Germany, Italy, and Ukraine, reporting more than 10 000 new cases in the past 24 hours. Another 22 countries reported more than 1000 cases, and an additional 6 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 8.4% of daily case numbers and 6.1% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 7.51 million cases. Iran reported the highest number of cases (10 250) over the last 24 hours, followed by Jordan, Iraq, Pakistan, Lebanon, UAE, Palestinian Authority, Kuwait, Oman, and Tunisia. Bahrain, Morocco, Saudi Arabia, Libya, Qatar, and Egypt reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 1.8% of daily case numbers and 2.7 % of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 3.08 million cases. Ethiopia (1976) reported the highest number of cases over last 24 hours followed by Kenya (1530), Botswana (1382), and Reunion (1025). South Africa reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Cameroon, Gabon, and South Sudan, among others, did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 2.7% of daily case numbers and 0.5% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 1.90 million cases. Philippines reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 9000 cases), followed by Japan, Malaysia, South Korea, Mongolia, and Papua New Guinea.

- The South East Asia region reported 12.5% of the daily newly reported cases and 6.5% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 14.82 million cases. India is dominant, reporting over 53 000 cases, followed by Bangladesh (5042), Indonesia (4682), Maldives and Nepal (167 cases each), and Sri Lanka (139).

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 31 March 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

